options.content: AWS Elemental MediaPackage

AWS Elemental MediaPackage is a just-in-time video packaging and origination service that runs in the AWS Cloud. With MediaPackage, you can deliver highly secure, scalable, and reliable video streams to a wide variety of playback devices and content delivery networks (CDNs).

For more information on configuring this integration, please visit our documentation.

targets.rawSql:
SELECT uniq(clientIp)
FROM __PROJECT_NAME__.__EGRESS_TABLE__
WHERE channelId = '${v_MediaPackage_Channel}'
  AND position(request, '.ts') > 0
  AND timestamp > subtractMinutes(NOW(), 10)

panels.description: Number of bytes that MediaPackage successfully sends for each request. If MediaPackage doesn't receive any requests for output in the specified interval, then no data is given.

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  timestamp, labels['Channel'] AS "Channel", value['sum'] AS "Egress Bytes"
FROM
    __PROJECT_NAME__.__METRICS_TABLE__
WHERE metric_name = 'EgressBytes'
AND labels['Channel'] = '${v_MediaPackage_Channel}'
AND mapContains(labels, 'Channel')
AND length(mapKeys(labels)) = 1
AND $__timeFilter(timestamp)
ORDER BY timestamp DESC, "Channel" ASC

panels.title: Total Egress Bytes

panels.description: Number of bytes of content that AWS Elemental MediaPackage receives for each input request. If MediaPackage doesn't receive any requests for input in the specified interval, then no data is given.

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  timestamp, labels['Channel'] AS "Channel", value['sum'] AS "Ingress Bytes"
FROM
  __PROJECT_NAME__.__METRICS_TABLE__
WHERE metric_name = 'IngressBytes'
AND labels['Channel'] = '${v_MediaPackage_Channel}'
AND mapContains(labels, 'Channel')
AND length(mapKeys(labels)) = 1
AND $__timeFilter(timestamp)
ORDER BY timestamp DESC, "Channel" ASC

panels.title: Total Ingress Bytes (All Endpoints)

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  timestamp, labels['Channel'] AS "Channel", labels['StatusCodeRange'] AS "Status Code Range", value['sum'] AS "Egress Request Count"
FROM
  __PROJECT_NAME__.__METRICS_TABLE__
WHERE metric_name = 'EgressRequestCount'
AND labels['Channel'] = '${v_MediaPackage_Channel}'
AND mapContains(labels, 'Channel')
AND mapContains(labels, 'StatusCodeRange')
AND length(mapKeys(labels)) = 2
AND $__timeFilter(timestamp)
ORDER BY timestamp DESC, "Channel" ASC

panels.title: Total Requests Per Status Code Range (All Endpoints)

panels.description: Number of bytes that MediaPackage successfully sends for each request. If MediaPackage doesn't receive any requests for output in the specified interval, then no data is given.

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  timestamp, labels['OriginEndpoint'] AS "Origin Endpoint", value['sum'] AS "Sum Egress Bytes"
FROM
  __PROJECT_NAME__.__METRICS_TABLE__
WHERE metric_name = 'EgressBytes'
AND labels['Channel'] = '${v_MediaPackage_Channel}'
AND mapContains(labels, 'OriginEndpoint')
AND $__timeFilter(timestamp)
ORDER BY timestamp DESC, "Origin Endpoint" ASC

panels.title: Egress Bytes

panels.description: The time that it takes MediaPackage to process each output request. If MediaPackage doesn't receive any requests for output in the specified interval, then no data is given.

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  timestamp, labels['OriginEndpoint'] AS "Origin Endpoint", (value['sum'] / value['count']) AS "Average Egress Response Time"
FROM
  __PROJECT_NAME__.__METRICS_TABLE__
WHERE metric_name = 'EgressResponseTime'
AND labels['Channel'] = '${v_MediaPackage_Channel}'
AND mapContains(labels, 'OriginEndpoint')
AND $__timeFilter(timestamp)
ORDER BY timestamp DESC, "Origin Endpoint" ASC

panels.title: Egress Response Time (Average)

targets.rawSql:
WITH (
  SELECT topK(50)(clientIp)
  FROM __PROJECT_NAME__.__EGRESS_TABLE__
  WHERE channelId = '${v_MediaPackage_Channel}'
    AND $__timeFilter(timestamp)
) AS top_50_clientIp

SELECT
    clientIp AS "Client IP",
    count() AS "Count"
FROM __PROJECT_NAME__.__EGRESS_TABLE__
WHERE channelId = '${v_MediaPackage_Channel}'
  AND has(top_50_clientIp, clientIp)
  AND $__timeFilter(timestamp)
GROUP BY clientIp
ORDER BY count() DESC

WITH (
  SELECT topK(50)(userAgent)
  FROM __PROJECT_NAME__.__EGRESS_TABLE__
  WHERE channelId = '${v_MediaPackage_Channel}'
    AND $__timeFilter(timestamp)
) AS top_50_useragent

SELECT
    userAgent AS "User Agent",
    count() AS "Count"
FROM __PROJECT_NAME__.__EGRESS_TABLE__
WHERE channelId = '${v_MediaPackage_Channel}'
  AND $__timeFilter(timestamp)
GROUP BY userAgent
ORDER BY count() DESC

SELECT timestamp, concat(endpointId, ' - ', method, ' - ', statusCode, ' - ', request), endpointId, request, clientIp, protocol, method, statusCode, processingTime, sentBytes, userAgent, domainName
FROM __PROJECT_NAME__.__EGRESS_TABLE__
WHERE 
channelId = '${v_MediaPackage_Channel}'
  AND $__timeFilter(timestamp)
ORDER BY timestamp DESC
LIMIT 1000
